attachments.title: Google I/O Extended 2015
attachments.text: Join us for the live stream of the keynote from Google I/O with your host Peter Friese. I/O is Google&#39;s annual developer celebration and a chance to get together with like minded folks to hear what&#39;s new from Google in the next 12 months. Our mission is to create excitement and buzz in the London Developer community - we encourage you to share, contribute and voice your opinions about the new announcements. However, we don’t want to stop there! Post I/O let’s keep momentum in these discussions through communities, social media and the workplace. We will introduce you to community leaders who will point you in the right direction to support your exploration in their areas of expertise. Agenda: 6pm - 8pm Keynote (aired on every screen throughout campus London) 8pm - 11pm Silent Disco (Selected talks shown silent disco style on the 3rd floor) 8pm - 11pm Breakout workshop and discussion sessions (divided into zones of interest with a community leader hosting the discussion) Aside from the awesome content we will provide you with plenty of Food, Drink and of course - SWAG!
